Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.31,0:01:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,long time since we've been here and this is like a whole home week here and we
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.78,0:01:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,were in snow for you we thought that would be nice create a creative life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.68,0:01:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,actually rains the snow and we want to thank them for it yes thank you for the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.52,0:01:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,snow sweetheart we we she said she had a surprise for us and so don't even do
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.90,0:01:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,things like that elsewhere in the world you're stuck with the weather here we
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.78,0:01:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,just create it whatever suits us what happened to the music anyway the magic
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.68,0:02:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,music well and to celebrate today we we heard from a publisher in Russia we're
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.98,0:02:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,gonna be in Russian now so like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're in Russian we're in Slavovian we're in Slovenian we're in all different
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.98,0:02:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,languages so that's very nice and I brought my ego with me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.09,0:04:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to see if it was working well let's see I forgot about what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.43,0:04:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,today's lecture is about does anybody know illuminating thought alright last one yes retry
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.93,0:04:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was in the laboratory uh and I remember there was this seminar this guy was so interested in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.88,0:04:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Community Studies very similar to what Mr. Bogen doesn't like and I mean really knows everything
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.12,0:04:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,he's into He knows where his boy gets whatever he has to hide what he has to hide here so so i don't
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.14,0:04:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh oh she does this investors an investigation not on my existing circuitry one before we know what a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.40,0:04:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of these protocols go I guess was so Daar ratio where people think i'm not even an artist I'm an instructor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.33,0:04:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any thoughts about the lecture today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.57,0:04:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll have to wing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.58,0:04:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, since we last were here, we've been all around the country and talked here and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've discovered that it's better to start the lecture from the end and work back to the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll start with the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.21,0:05:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you don't have to listen to the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.59,0:05:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Today has to do with, I believe, transcending thought. Isn't that what it's about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.59,0:05:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with a condition that is already in existence
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.68,0:05:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and how to just become aware that it's already there and that you don't have to do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.34,0:05:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can save many lifetimes by just getting a simple understanding of how things come about in the world, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.08,0:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And it'll save you all kinds of worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a group like this, which calibrates quite high,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.28,0:05:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the obstruction to enlightenment is really the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.76,0:05:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,For 85% of the population on the planet today,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.73,0:06:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the problem is really to cross over 200 to become oriented and to value integrity, truth, and honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.34,0:06:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And in America now, 51% of the people calibrate over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.37,0:06:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In 4090,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.19,0:06:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,15% are trudging along.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.51,0:06:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And we hope to inspire them to move faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.03,0:06:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a group like this, which has already decided that they'll give up murder and robbery and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.82,0:06:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and thievery is a lifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.10,0:06:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,give up recidivism and live in the world instead of a prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.16,0:06:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,um,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,um,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.55,0:06:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the problem is, therefore, the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.65,0:06:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, each level on the scale, I've got a new pointer thing, but I don't know where it is here, someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.84,0:07:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Someplace, it's in my, somewhere, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.88,0:07:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we, we, oh, there it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.40,0:07:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so new, I don't even know I have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.05,0:07:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.02,0:07:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ta-da!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.45,0:07:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The world, uh, you know, the world over time, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand the ego is to not be at the effect of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.96,0:07:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that it's a development that occurred over great eons of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.90,0:07:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a slide on the eons of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.12,0:07:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Over great millennia, then life appeared at consciousness level one, as bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.92,0:07:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.60,0:07:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Algae and viruses don't have any consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.98,0:08:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask me why. Apparently they don't think about anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't until you get to a bacteria that you start to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.03,0:08:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Bacteria, Calvary said, won. We'll get to that slide later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.03,0:08:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, great millennia, on through the animal kingdom, on up through the Komodo dragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.05,0:08:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's level Bin Laden.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.05,0:08:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he calibrates the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.05,0:08:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Up through the reptiles, and then we get to domestic animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.05,0:08:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally we get to the capacity over 200 herbivores.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.95,0:08:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The grass eaters calibrate about 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.14,0:08:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you get on to the scale of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.14,0:08:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.46,0:08:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.78,0:08:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.78,0:09:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Neanderthal man, about 75 here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.78,0:09:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Neanderthal man really wasn't man, he was pre-man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.39,0:09:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Neanderthal didn't evolve into Homo erectus or Homo sapien.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.39,0:09:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He got off the train there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.39,0:09:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Being smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.39,0:09:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He got off. And he disappeared into oblivion and reemerged then later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.52,0:09:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Off the evolutionary tree is Homo erectus
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.52,0:09:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and Homo erectus and 600,000 years ago finally Homo sapiens,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.52,0:09:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Idelta, appeared in Ethiopia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.52,0:09:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,At about this consciousness level here, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.89,0:09:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it took many, many centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.89,0:09:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of Buddha, the consciousness level of man was 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.47,0:09:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of Jesus Christ, the consciousness level of mankind was 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.60,0:10:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at the teachings of the ancient masters,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.64,0:10:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to realize to whom they were talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.64,0:10:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To whom they were talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.64,0:10:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, over a great millennia of time, it got up to 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.64,0:10:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It stayed at 190, below the level of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.64,0:10:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then recently, in the late 80s, crossed over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.96,0:10:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, when we were in San Francisco,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.02,0:10:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,right during the session, at the end of the session,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.02,0:10:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it went from 205 to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.02,0:10:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the time of the last,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.02,0:10:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, harmonic concordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.40,0:10:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And we happened to be talking to a large group in San Francisco,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.40,0:10:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and we calibrated the level of consciousness at 515.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.40,0:10:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was supposed to happen from 518 to 530,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.44,0:10:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,San Francisco time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.72,0:10:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And in front of a whole audience, and it's on video,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.72,0:10:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we did the calibrated level of mankind at quarter after five.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.72,0:10:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we all did OM,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.72,0:11:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and other wondrous things, and prayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.92,0:11:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And by God, at 530,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.92,0:11:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level jumped from 205 to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.01,0:11:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have a new millennia in which we're living.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.01,0:11:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At 207, non-integrity tends to surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, at 190, it's just everybody does business that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.14,0:11:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A few bucks under the table,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.14,0:11:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,a little wink here, a little wink there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.14,0:11:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The old boy network,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.68,0:11:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which, as Wall Street has found out,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.68,0:11:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't working out anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.68,0:11:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The old boy network doesn't work anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.75,0:11:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And interestingly enough, along with the old boy network,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that the women CEOs,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.64,0:11:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the companies run by women CEOs,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.64,0:11:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,according to Fortune magazine,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.64,0:11:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,were more profitable than the corporations run by men.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.64,0:11:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Considerably more, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.96,0:12:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Like 30% more profitable than the ones run by men.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.25,0:12:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.25,0:12:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.84,0:12:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, women are making tremendous executives.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.84,0:12:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I was saying to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.84,0:12:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,now why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.84,0:12:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I saw it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.84,0:12:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because men come from a different culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.84,0:12:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the old boy network,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.84,0:12:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you do me a favor, I do you a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.84,0:12:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, many years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.84,0:12:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody offered me an insider,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.84,0:12:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it would get you prosecuted nowadays,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.84,0:12:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.84,0:12:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, he ran the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.20,0:12:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he said, give me 10,000
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.20,0:12:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll give you 100,000 back in a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.20,0:12:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I didn't do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.80,0:12:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but probably because I didn't have 10,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.83,0:12:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually, by that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.86,0:12:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity, it would create guilt, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.86,0:12:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, in the old boy network,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.86,0:12:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,then, amongst men,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.86,0:13:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,certain deviations from
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.86,0:13:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute purity have been part of the culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.86,0:13:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not part of the women's culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.86,0:13:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Not part of the women's culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.86,0:13:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And when women first appeared as CEOs,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.86,0:13:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the guys all thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.86,0:13:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,boy, they're really picky uni,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.86,0:13:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.86,0:13:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Really picky uni people, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.86,0:13:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they're new at the job,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.53,0:13:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No, women don't come from that culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.53,0:13:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not from the old boy culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.53,0:13:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they toe the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.95,0:13:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I predict, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.95,0:13:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in a few generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.95,0:13:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll be the old girl culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.59,0:13:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see somebody off your board
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.59,0:13:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll see to it that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.59,0:13:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,things go your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.59,0:13:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But they haven't learned that yet, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.59,0:13:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I just think that's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.39,0:13:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I find a lot of women don't know that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.39,0:13:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so I thought they should know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.39,0:14:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That isn't what we're talking about today, anyway, but.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.22,0:14:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.56,0:14:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.56,0:14:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.43,0:14:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not spiritual practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.65,0:14:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not specific techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.65,0:14:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not sitting in weird positions
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.88,0:14:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and breathing in strange ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not getting your aura read.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.53,0:14:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Your cards told,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.17,0:14:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,your ruins thrown,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.17,0:14:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,your marbles, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.47,0:14:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,New Ageism won't get you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.47,0:14:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It will get you in latent,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.47,0:14:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but it will satisfy your curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.92,0:14:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible to get involved
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.92,0:14:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then become uninvolved, unscathed,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.92,0:14:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's unlikely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.20,0:14:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because usually some of it sticks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.20,0:14:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I advise people to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.65,0:15:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.65,0:15:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's hidden energies,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.65,0:15:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the likes of which you're unaware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.65,0:15:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,People are naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.72,0:15:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside of,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.72,0:15:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of the human condition
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.72,0:15:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is really not evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not really even ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's naivete.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.72,0:15:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't know any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.72,0:15:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's attracted by the lure of the unusual,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.00,0:15:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the unique,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.13,0:15:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the odd,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.13,0:15:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the bizarre.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.13,0:15:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Bamba Rumba
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.64,0:15:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,giving you instructions from the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.64,0:15:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.95,0:15:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,God help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.65,0:15:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.65,0:15:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.80,0:15:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness then evolves up to the point
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.80,0:15:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,where integrity now is the rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.96,0:15:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.96,0:15:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read for weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.96,0:15:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has had the impact of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.96,0:15:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.96,0:15:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly something that's been getting away with something
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.96,0:16:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for a long, long time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.96,0:16:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is suddenly under the spotlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.96,0:16:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a good time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.18,0:16:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to pull fast ones in the business world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.18,0:16:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.18,0:16:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday the president of Smith & Wesson
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.18,0:16:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,gets knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.98,0:16:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He really has a criminal record.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.98,0:16:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And he didn't think it was important
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.98,0:16:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell anybody about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.98,0:16:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.32,0:16:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,17 years in prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.67,0:16:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not important.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.28,0:16:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.28,0:16:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree that he's turned a corner
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.28,0:16:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and has become an okay person.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.28,0:16:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really don't doubt his integrity nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.28,0:16:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.37,0:16:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that he didn't reveal it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.37,0:16:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,put his company at great risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.37,0:16:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his company should have known better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.56,0:16:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't get a background check on executives
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,before they get big salaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.56,0:16:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they need to be examined.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.56,0:16:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the board of directors is also careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.66,0:16:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because integrity means
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.92,0:16:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that you also demand integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.92,0:16:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's your style of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.92,0:17:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the new lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.17,0:17:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single day there's been
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.17,0:17:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a scandal of dereliction
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.17,0:17:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from the level of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.17,0:17:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which did not happen in the old days.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.17,0:17:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In the old days,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.17,0:17:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,there weren't big scandals,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.17,0:17:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,much less every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.17,0:17:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,much less in the headlines,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.17,0:17:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,much less celebrities.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.61,0:17:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.61,0:17:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So today has to do with thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.18,0:17:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.18,0:17:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,transcending thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.38,0:17:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The transcendence of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.38,0:17:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is automatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.38,0:17:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something you have to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.96,0:17:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,acquire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.96,0:17:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.28,0:17:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from a way of contextualizing yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.56,0:17:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and contextualizing life
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.82,0:17:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you become
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.88,0:17:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is thoughtless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.04,0:18:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that which is thoughtless
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.04,0:18:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of how you contextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.04,0:18:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the meaning of your life
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.04,0:18:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the meaning of life altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.46,0:18:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does the mind think at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.03,0:18:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does the mind think at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.03,0:18:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.28,0:18:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind really thinks because of anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.28,0:18:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and because of safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.28,0:18:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It really thinks because of survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.28,0:18:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to do with this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.28,0:18:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.43,0:18:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I guess you hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.65,0:18:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.65,0:18:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I never know what the body's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.65,0:18:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.65,0:18:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what do I do with this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.65,0:18:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to do with this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.65,0:18:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.83,0:18:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why people around are very useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.83,0:18:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You say,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.83,0:18:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what is that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.83,0:18:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You say,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.83,0:18:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you hit that and you get a spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.83,0:18:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.83,0:18:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa, that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.83,0:18:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.83,0:19:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't really have to know anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.71,0:19:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody around knows
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.71,0:19:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and as long as somebody knows,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.71,0:19:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.71,0:19:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you understand the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.18,0:19:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.18,0:19:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,thought comes to a slow intermittency
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.50,0:19:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of a continuous process
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.50,0:19:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that's torture.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.59,0:19:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's really no necessity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.59,0:19:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to think about anything
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.59,0:19:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,once you understand who you are
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.59,0:19:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and what life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.59,0:19:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What does the mind usually do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.50,0:19:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks about the future
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.50,0:19:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it thinks about the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.50,0:19:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It ruminates about the past
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.01,0:19:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.56,0:19:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if the ego is determining
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.56,0:19:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,your perception now,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.56,0:19:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it did also in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.16,0:19:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't remember reality
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.36,0:19:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.36,0:20:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only remember
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.36,0:20:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego's perceptions
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.55,0:20:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which are all distorted and BS.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.55,0:20:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's nothing in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.71,0:20:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.71,0:20:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And as much as it's not real,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.74,0:20:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in ruminating
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.74,0:20:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying to correct it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.74,0:20:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I'd said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.74,0:20:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I'd done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.93,0:20:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to handle the past
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.93,0:20:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,was well expressed by Bill Wilson
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.93,0:20:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,who was the founder of AA,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.93,0:20:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,who had an enlightening experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.03,0:20:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,was transformed,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.03,0:20:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a good part of society
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and introduced
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.03,0:20:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and made us realize
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.03,0:20:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the healing power
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.03,0:20:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.03,0:20:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill said,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.99,0:20:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,there's only one thing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.99,0:20:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you gotta do about the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.99,0:20:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,have a decent regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.17,0:20:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a decent regret
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.17,0:20:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and live differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.17,0:20:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,End of story.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.17,0:20:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that agreeable to everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.65,0:20:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A decent regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.68,0:20:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say if you were God,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.80,0:20:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what would you say to a person?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.80,0:20:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You killed all those people, man,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.80,0:20:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and you slaughtered all them people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.80,0:20:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sorry?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.80,0:21:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.80,0:21:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.93,0:21:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You're forgiven.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.44,0:21:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's not sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.44,0:21:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you send him back to light world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.44,0:21:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and let him live it all over again
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.44,0:21:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,until he's sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.44,0:21:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.92,0:21:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You just stay there until you're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.50,0:21:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that what it's all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.23,0:21:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've realized
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.23,0:21:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.23,0:21:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for what happened in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.23,0:21:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're gonna accept
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.23,0:21:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,a new way of living,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.23,0:21:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what more is there to life?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.23,0:21:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.23,0:21:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.35,0:21:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We just took care of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.80,0:21:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All your memories of the past
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.40,0:21:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,are distorted perceptions
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.60,0:21:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you went through the past
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.11,0:21:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in an enlightened state,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.11,0:22:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't remember anything about it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.17,0:22:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because nothing happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.17,0:22:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing to recall
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.17,0:22:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,except projections.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.65,0:22:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see they're all projections,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.65,0:22:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they lose their lure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.65,0:22:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.90,0:22:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the future has to do with anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.19,0:22:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.32,0:22:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with anticipated disasters
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.32,0:22:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and misfortunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.32,0:22:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we run out of gas
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.32,0:22:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on the highway, et cetera?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.92,0:22:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What if the world's gonna be hit by a meteor?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.92,0:22:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.92,0:22:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,predicting the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.95,0:22:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of all the fortunes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.95,0:22:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that have been made
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.95,0:22:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,by various people
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.95,0:22:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,predicting the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.95,0:22:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a new book.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.24,0:22:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It usually comes out
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.24,0:22:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of some mystical thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.24,0:22:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,like you count the number of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.24,0:22:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,whiskers in a seal's mustache,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.43,0:22:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and you multiply that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.43,0:22:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,by the stones in the pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.43,0:22:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You divide that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.43,0:22:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,by the number of chapters
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.43,0:22:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of books in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.43,0:22:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You multiply that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:22:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,by a sacred number,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.43,0:23:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and you come up with 5082.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.43,0:23:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, man,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.49,0:23:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll give you a new date.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.49,0:23:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is coming to an end
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.49,0:23:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in 5082.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.49,0:23:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that affect your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.77,0:23:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.64,0:23:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,See, all these books
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.64,0:23:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that predict the end of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.64,0:23:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.64,0:23:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.64,0:23:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,wants to buy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.64,0:23:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not gonna be here,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.64,0:23:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.05,0:23:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They said next week
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.05,0:23:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd be worth reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.95,0:23:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In Sedona,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.95,0:23:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got all kinds
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.95,0:23:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of people like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.95,0:23:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.95,0:23:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has a funny way
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.95,0:23:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of making his hair and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.95,0:23:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.95,0:23:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,every five or ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.95,0:23:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,he's got a new prediction.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.95,0:23:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So then,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.95,0:23:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.95,0:23:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,if I predict
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.95,0:23:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the world's gonna end
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.95,0:23:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in such and such a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.95,0:23:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and it didn't, man,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.95,0:23:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd just fold up my tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.80,0:23:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd just say,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.80,0:23:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,oops,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.80,0:23:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and find something else to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.80,0:23:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.96,0:23:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,These people don't even have that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.96,0:23:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.96,0:23:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.96,0:23:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they come back next year,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.41,0:23:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they got a new prediction
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.41,0:23:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that they counted
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.41,0:24:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the ruins
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.41,0:24:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Temple of Karnak wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.41,0:24:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,measured it in sacred geometry,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.41,0:24:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and came up with 2043.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.41,0:24:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.48,0:24:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.48,0:24:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I always tell these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're gonna predict
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.48,0:24:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the end of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.48,0:24:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,make it far in the future, man,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.57,0:24:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so that when they're all gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.57,0:24:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody will ever know
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.57,0:24:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.57,0:24:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who have
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.57,0:24:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a decent regret,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.57,0:24:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a really heartfelt regret,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.57,0:24:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,are the ones
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.57,0:24:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,who have a decent regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.96,0:24:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the ones
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.18,0:24:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who have a decent regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.18,0:24:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the ones
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.18,0:24:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who have a heartfelt regret
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.18,0:24:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for human error.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.37,0:24:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.37,0:24:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the human is built,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.37,0:24:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he's fallible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.37,0:24:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.37,0:24:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,errors are certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.37,0:24:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you haven't made
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.37,0:24:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,serious errors in your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.37,0:24:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.37,0:24:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,To say you haven't made
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.37,0:24:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,serious errors in your life
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.37,0:24:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is already a serious error.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.37,0:24:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We've all screwed up mindily,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.37,0:24:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.37,0:24:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.37,0:24:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.37,0:24:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.37,0:24:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.37,0:24:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.37,0:24:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.37,0:24:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.37,0:24:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.37,0:24:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.37,0:24:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.37,0:24:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.47,0:24:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.47,0:25:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.76,0:25:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.76,0:25:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.76,0:25:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.76,0:25:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.76,0:25:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.76,0:25:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.01,0:25:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.01,0:25:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.03,0:25:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.03,0:25:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.38,0:25:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.38,0:25:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.38,0:25:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.38,0:25:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.38,0:25:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.38,0:25:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.38,0:25:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.38,0:25:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.38,0:25:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.38,0:25:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.38,0:25:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.38,0:25:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.38,0:25:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.38,0:25:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.38,0:25:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.38,0:25:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.38,0:25:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.38,0:25:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.38,0:25:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.38,0:25:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as Christ said, forgive them for they know not what they do,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.89,0:25:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Buddha said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.62,0:25:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So the one sin of the past from which all human beings suffer
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.52,0:25:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is ignorance, not knowing the full truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.20,0:25:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a condition of all of society, and it doesn't make you special.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.24,0:25:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord, I've sinned.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.51,0:25:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,People make a big drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.93,0:26:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a whole trip about ashes and sackcloth and suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.53,0:26:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and self-flagellation and guilt and misery,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.53,0:26:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are people that are looking for God at the bottom of the chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.42,0:26:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame, guilt, griefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.20,0:26:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, how I have sinned.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.00,0:26:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that gets rid of a little guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.22,0:26:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I'm not going to put it down,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.63,0:26:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,except after a while you feel guilty that you did that,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.67,0:26:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's beside the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.70,0:26:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking for God down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.64,0:26:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I heard a lecture that said he was up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.34,0:26:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and that changed my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.92,0:26:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.54,0:26:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So everything in the past then is washed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.96,0:27:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to think about the past because there's no reality there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.20,0:27:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were in a state of reality, as I said, there wouldn't be any past.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.70,0:27:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the next thing is fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.69,0:27:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear has to do with not realizing that you're safe at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.33,0:27:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the brain and the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.60,0:27:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they manufacture conditions and take examples from the past
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.23,0:27:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and justify that fear is a rational condition
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.55,0:27:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have to think fearfully of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.52,0:27:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So the future then has to do with control,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.48,0:27:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to control the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.72,0:27:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All this is premised on survival is due to the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.69,0:27:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you get more sophisticated, you realize that,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.71,0:27:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,survival is not a product of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.77,0:27:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a product of the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.87,0:28:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind becomes silent automatically with the realization that you are absolutely safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.37,0:28:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if you aren't, so what?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.14,0:28:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.79,0:28:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dying is a certainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.68,0:28:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So accepting the certainty of death, then what can we do about the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.88,0:28:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be devoted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.04,0:28:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be devoted to all that is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.59,0:28:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Be devoted to beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.04,0:28:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Be devoted to all that is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.58,0:28:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the beauty, as we came here this morning, it was stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.90,0:28:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The only difficulty with beauty is it makes you cry,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.58,0:28:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you shouldn't be driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.27,0:28:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as you said, what are you crying about this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.07,0:28:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I don't know, it's just the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.39,0:29:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the snow in Sedona, you cry with happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.74,0:29:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, first time we've had it all year.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.09,0:29:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to be aware and to be aligned with, to honor divinity and all of its expressions,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.75,0:29:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to be sensitive to the beauty that exists at every moment in all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.90,0:29:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the spiritual pathway through this world is only a way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.23,0:29:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you become that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.96,0:29:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm not crazy about various techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.06,0:29:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Breathing and sitting in strange ways and contorting your body and sucking your stomach
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.20,0:29:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's against your spine and weird things.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.54,0:30:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only necessary to just be who you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.97,0:30:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a divine state.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.69,0:30:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And when walks through the world on the wings of truth, the divine state reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.83,0:30:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When you realize the truth of your own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.02,0:30:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, how you contextualize your life, then, is how you present yourself to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.02,0:30:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's what you are to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.05,0:30:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe responds in like.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.11,0:30:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When you are thus to the world, the world is thus to thee.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.75,0:30:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you walk safely through the hail of bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.94,0:30:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you walk safely through the hail of bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.94,0:30:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And you walk safely through the hail of bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.10,0:30:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And if one's meant for you, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.41,0:31:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you come out the other side, then there wasn't one meant for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.04,0:31:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is the way it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.04,0:31:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is complete surrender, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.55,0:31:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The past is eliminated by the realization that a decent regret is all that's necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.96,0:31:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make sure about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.15,0:31:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.41,0:31:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A decent heartfelt regret does indeed undo the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.94,0:31:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Lord, amen. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.97,0:31:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It does indeed undo the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.49,0:31:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In one instant, that's all it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.26,0:31:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can stop ruminating and trying to rewrite the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.60,0:31:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lying in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.62,0:31:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have said this, I shouldn't have said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.62,0:31:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have bought this stock, I should have bought this stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.80,0:31:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have bought that stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.50,0:32:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.36,0:32:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So the past was a learning program.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.68,0:32:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's the point of that learning?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.14,0:32:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The point of that learning is for you to have a decent regret about it and let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.52,0:32:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To stop dragging it around.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.54,0:32:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to hear other people's chains dragging.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.84,0:32:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They come up after a lecture and they want to give me about,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.52,0:32:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, I did this and I did that and then she died and I wasn't there
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.88,0:32:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and my mother-in-law was having her gallbladder out.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.95,0:32:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, oh boy, I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.37,0:32:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Susie's daughter says, you're the Bill O'Reilly of spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.86,0:32:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I just say to the lady, cut it out, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.58,0:32:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't drag me along with your sad story.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.96,0:32:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.86,0:32:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are people who, you see, wallow in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.94,0:33:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because their ego is sucking the juices out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.86,0:33:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the juices the ego gets out of wallowing in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.87,0:33:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,sackcloth and ashes, all the drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.95,0:33:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.00,0:33:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.36,0:33:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.48,0:33:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're also trying to control God and tell him what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.64,0:33:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive you because look how you suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.40,0:33:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's blackmail.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.91,0:33:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people try to blackmail God with suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.61,0:33:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize how you're trying?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.39,0:33:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a control thing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.42,0:33:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,God is this awful parent and if you just suffer and wallow in guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.37,0:33:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,then he'll forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.87,0:33:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to manipulate God because God is a condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.70,0:33:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-manipulable.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.61,0:33:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a giant electrostatic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.74,0:34:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.56,0:34:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.56,0:34:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The future then is surrendering to the will of God completely with no reservation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.51,0:34:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.37,0:34:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.05,0:34:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's letting go, wanting to control the world, control the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.33,0:34:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a negative view of yourself, then you expect the worst in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.29,0:34:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to plan for the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.77,0:34:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're extrapolating, you're projecting out there what you think you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.76,0:34:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think what you are at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.58,0:34:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be what you are and don't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.65,0:34:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you just be what you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.43,0:34:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it in one instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.01,0:34:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Be willing to accept what I'm saying to you right now with no reservation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.29,0:35:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that easy?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.94,0:35:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If I tell you E equals MC squared, I don't want some smartass to get up there
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.72,0:35:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and start to argue with the mathematics of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.60,0:35:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you E equals MC squared.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.22,0:35:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want some smartass to get up there and start to argue with the mathematics of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.44,0:35:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you E equals MC squared.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.50,0:35:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.72,0:35:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ, that's so simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.46,0:35:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, everybody can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.02,0:35:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.07,0:35:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just energy, condensed energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.71,0:35:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you don't have to even go to school to figure that one out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.17,0:35:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Once somebody explains it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.10,0:35:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So we accept things on faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.36,0:35:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We accept things on faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.53,0:35:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,To completely surrender one's will to God, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.29,0:35:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,means whatever happens in the future happens in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.76,0:35:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about the mind going silent and leaving us stranded.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.32,0:36:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I get letters from like that all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.72,0:36:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm meditating and my mind stops, and that scares me because how will I survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.70,0:36:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe you won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.86,0:36:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what she wants to survive for.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.70,0:36:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,She's all the way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.25,0:36:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not just be there?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.57,0:36:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.92,0:36:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let God worry about the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.75,0:36:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the world worry about the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.75,0:36:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this week one came that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.52,0:36:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We said, let God worry about the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.81,0:36:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you bliss out, you bliss out.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.26,0:36:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody blisses out, you sit them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.26,0:36:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You put a tin cup next to them, and people walk by.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.26,0:36:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother-in-law comes and gets the cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.73,0:36:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Empties it every hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.73,0:37:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Children are okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.59,0:37:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.92,0:37:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So we let go of wanting to change the past, and we let go of wanting to control the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.59,0:37:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's done at a profound depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.59,0:37:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,One realizes that you are safe, not because it says so in a book, but because you realize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.49,0:37:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,As I stand here, you don't see any past hanging off of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.08,0:37:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You see any past anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.27,0:37:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see any past.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.91,0:37:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When is a karmic product at this moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.00,0:37:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That which stands here is where evolution is at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.18,0:37:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.01,0:37:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The present is the finish of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.01,0:38:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,With spiritual realization, which you come by through contemplation, it's really a contemplative matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.04,0:38:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As you walk about, you say, who am I to myself anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.13,0:38:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Who am I to the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.44,0:38:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I to life?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.44,0:38:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What is my relationship to life?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.74,0:38:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When you reverence all that is beautiful, when you reverence all that is divine by virtue of its existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.61,0:38:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,then you walk about in a different state.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.61,0:38:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that state arises a conviction of safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.15,0:38:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind will start up periodically when it needs to tell you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.70,0:38:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because it's coming from the mind, but because it's coming from the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.70,0:39:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need to know something, the spirit will see to it that you remember to take your vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.92,0:39:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.94,0:39:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes credit for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.94,0:39:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's really the spirit acting through your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.71,0:39:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Who sees to it that you eat and all those things?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.71,0:39:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,She has a big thing about eating, I don't know, every few days I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.74,0:39:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people are concerned about the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.08,0:39:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not concerned about the body, other people worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.08,0:39:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need to eat something, somebody will tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.40,0:39:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to think about when will I eat next or what am I going to eat next
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.40,0:39:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's all handled.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.36,0:39:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all handled by the nature of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.36,0:40:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want everybody here to feel profoundly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.38,0:40:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safe from your past.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.38,0:40:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anybody here who lacks a decent regret for the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.38,0:40:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.44,0:40:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.26,0:40:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who doesn't have a decent regret for the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.33,0:40:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We just confirmed that that's all you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.52,0:40:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to invoke God's mercy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.49,0:40:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to invoke the mercy of an electrostatic condenser.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.68,0:40:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When you put a charge, it crackles.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.68,0:40:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When there's no charge, it doesn't crackle.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.68,0:40:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't say, oh dear electrostatic condenser, give me the presence of thy presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.03,0:40:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The past is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.72,0:40:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you only have to look at the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.72,0:40:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The future you surrender to God
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.10,0:41:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so you don't have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.10,0:41:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That leaves you in the present, whatever that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.77,0:41:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Does anybody have any thoughts about the present?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.40,0:41:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to make one up, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.30,0:41:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't really have any thoughts about the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.70,0:41:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so if you give up wallowing in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.70,0:41:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying to rewrite history and make yourself look better,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.70,0:41:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,cleaner, brighter, and smarter,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.92,0:41:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't have to worry about your survival in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.92,0:41:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing's going on in the present as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.30,0:41:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.30,0:41:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's nothing for the mind to think about.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.03,0:41:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind becomes silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.92,0:41:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, the mind doesn't have to become silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.92,0:41:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.53,0:42:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.18,0:42:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Shading the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.34,0:42:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shading the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.38,0:42:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.38,0:42:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were sending me mysterious signals or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.49,0:42:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.49,0:42:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, when you have to think,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.58,0:42:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,all of a sudden a thought comes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.58,0:42:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It says,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.58,0:42:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a thought of curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.58,0:42:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What is she doing with that car there?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.09,0:42:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't have to worry that I won't think about things
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.09,0:42:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,when I should think about things.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.09,0:42:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.18,0:42:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You surrender your thoughts to God
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.18,0:42:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because they aren't worth anything anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.18,0:42:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,other than E equals MC squared,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.18,0:42:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't know what that means anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.92,0:42:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All I'm saying is we take certain things on faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.14,0:42:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We take certain things on faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.14,0:42:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That somebody who has been there
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.53,0:43:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,will tell you how it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.53,0:43:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and you just say,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.53,0:43:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, the big mistake is to argue with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.90,0:43:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Marco Polo went to China, he came back,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.18,0:43:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm sure a lot of people thought he was making up stories,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.18,0:43:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but that was their problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.07,0:43:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been to China,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.07,0:43:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,just the way he said it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.07,0:43:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chinese are very Chinese-y.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.87,0:43:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I can say.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.87,0:43:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.87,0:43:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith and confidence, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.41,0:43:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.05,0:43:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we're talking about is faith and confidence in wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.06,0:43:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll talk about what wisdom is,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.06,0:43:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,how it expresses itself
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.06,0:43:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.06,0:43:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.66,0:43:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Where were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.66,0:43:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about not thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.66,0:43:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which leads us in the middle of nowhere, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.66,0:44:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do we go from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.06,0:44:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people are here for the first time?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.06,0:44:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my gracious me, oh, my, oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.31,0:44:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then we'll have to hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.31,0:44:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.66,0:44:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,On with the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.66,0:44:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We're working on a new book,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.25,0:44:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.02,0:44:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.86,0:44:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,well, it's gonna be something.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.85,0:44:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Just trying to decide on a title.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.33,0:44:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.33,0:44:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, how about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.62,0:44:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.86,0:44:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the map of consciousness is all over the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.86,0:44:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to work the Internet, but people do.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.86,0:44:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And they give me all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.86,0:44:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're all over the Internet,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.86,0:44:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,all different languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.86,0:44:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So whatever we're talking about seems to have
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.98,0:45:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,some general recognition of its essential truth
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.98,0:45:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and its usefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.24,0:45:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind has never had any means
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.24,0:45:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of discerning truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.24,0:45:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.24,0:45:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to discern truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.24,0:45:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is limited to a small percentage of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.24,0:45:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The kinesiologic technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.84,0:45:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which itself calibrates at 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.84,0:45:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore is not explicable in logical terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.90,0:45:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it is only useful
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.21,0:45:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,if, for people whose own consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.21,0:45:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates 200 or over.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.21,0:45:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So that eliminates about 85,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.40,0:45:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,80% of the world, 85% of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.40,0:45:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, and then the question itself
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.01,0:45:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be integrous as far as motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.01,0:45:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So two people who are integrous
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.01,0:45:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,ask an integrous question,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.46,0:45:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way they get a correct answer
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.46,0:45:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is because they're dedicated to truth
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.46,0:46:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than looking for a position.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.46,0:46:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A positionality or a gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.65,0:46:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people usually don't get the right answers
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.65,0:46:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the intention behind it,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.13,0:46:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which is rather glaringly obvious very often.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.79,0:46:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to get the correct answer is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.79,0:46:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to say in the name of the highest truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.79,0:46:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.79,0:46:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask, O Lord, is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.79,0:46:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this or that or the other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.23,0:46:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So then you make a statement,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.23,0:46:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and you ask the person to quickly resist,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.23,0:46:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and as we said
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.30,0:46:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,before, the acupuncture system
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.19,0:46:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is very, very rapid.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.48,0:46:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I hold something in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.48,0:46:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and press down her arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.48,0:46:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a flash down.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.48,0:46:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She's strong right for a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.48,0:46:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but if I keep pushing,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.48,0:46:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that moment is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.48,0:46:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So some people wait too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.79,0:46:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we demonstrate it,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.79,0:46:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how quickly we do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.79,0:46:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We say we just want to confirm
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.79,0:47:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the validity of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.79,0:47:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that what we just said is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.79,0:47:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to tell her what I'm holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.79,0:47:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I can say to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.79,0:47:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm holding in mind is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.11,0:47:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's do it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.87,0:47:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in mind now is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.87,0:47:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding now in mind is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.09,0:47:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding now in mind is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.73,0:47:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't know what I was holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.73,0:47:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't know if I'm holding a hippopotamus,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.92,0:47:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a zebra.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.27,0:47:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No way of knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.26,0:47:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quick and easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.30,0:47:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are adept at it, others are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.30,0:47:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like riding a bicycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.30,0:47:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.33,0:47:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They get on the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.87,0:47:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like riding a horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.87,0:47:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried riding a horse for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.97,0:47:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I got thrown about 20 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.97,0:47:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Horses and I didn't get along until just recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.15,0:48:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, horses and I kissed and made up a course.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.60,0:48:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This horse actually was loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.60,0:48:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, whoa, a loving horse?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.60,0:48:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,One reason I didn't like them,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.89,0:48:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,they never seemed to be loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.91,0:48:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But this horse was actually affectionate.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.91,0:48:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, holy cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.91,0:48:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We took it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.91,0:48:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a picture of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.91,0:48:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This horse actually gave me a kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.91,0:48:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In that instant, horses and myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.91,0:48:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,now I have a lovely relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.91,0:48:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't ridden one since.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.66,0:48:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,My orthopedist doesn't recommend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.66,0:48:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One more fall, Doc, and you've had it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.06,0:48:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go on to number two.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.06,0:48:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to quickly run through the slides
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.06,0:48:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for those who haven't been here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.06,0:48:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.87,0:48:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm putting this in my right-hand pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.87,0:48:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.87,0:48:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my thingy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.47,0:49:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a mudra.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.75,0:49:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.33,0:49:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't some performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.67,0:49:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.47,0:49:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.02,0:49:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life is a presentation to divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.02,0:49:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the best that you can be
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.40,0:49:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment that you are what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.50,0:49:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life then is like a mudra.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.53,0:49:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life is like a sacred gift to the world and to God
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.55,0:49:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are being all that you can be at any given moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.51,0:49:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of all of life then
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.51,0:49:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,allows you to see the sacredness of your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.85,0:49:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That commitment to contextualize that that's why you're here,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.85,0:49:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to be all that you can be at any moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.85,0:49:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize the divinity of all things,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.85,0:50:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the beauty of all creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.55,0:50:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave judgment up to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.55,0:50:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,liberates you from thinking this,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.18,0:50:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the disease called thinking this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.34,0:50:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's go to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.34,0:50:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a contribution from Mr. Selinsky
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.37,0:50:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,whose name has been chopped off the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.37,0:50:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He translated the consciousness levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.62,0:50:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember I said they had to become logarithmic
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.62,0:50:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because the numbers are so huge, logarithmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.94,0:50:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a logarithmic scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.94,0:50:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we tried to give comparative in microwatts,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.46,0:50:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, just because people are used to such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.84,0:50:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're really talking about a nonlinear domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.84,0:50:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but to make it more comprehensible,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.84,0:50:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we tried to relate it in comparative figures
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.16,0:51:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to like the electromagnetic spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.47,0:51:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the things we write and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.47,0:51:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,people tend to become literal.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.04,0:51:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They tend to miss the forest for the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.39,0:51:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't focus on the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.39,0:51:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The things that we're trying to illustrate
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.39,0:51:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is so you get the gist of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.39,0:51:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The gist of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.39,0:51:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what he did was he translated...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.39,0:51:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He's very good at mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.39,0:51:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not very good at mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.39,0:51:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like mathematics, even.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.64,0:51:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.47,0:51:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, because it's so pedestrian.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.47,0:51:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're limited to trudging through the linear world.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.47,0:51:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.95,0:51:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're used to living free like a bird
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.95,0:51:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the nonlinear world,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.00,0:51:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a drag to have to figure everything out.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.00,0:51:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.54,0:52:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, he correlated it in microwatts
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.54,0:52:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,using more advanced mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.54,0:52:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The answers we got were using kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.63,0:52:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,which would make any dyed-in-the-wool scientist shudder.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.63,0:52:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where I figure out certain things.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.76,0:52:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, how much do I owe the government?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.76,0:52:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.76,0:52:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the right figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.66,0:52:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got employees that never give me a charge card.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.66,0:52:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, how much do we owe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.66,0:52:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we get the right amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.66,0:52:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I write them a check.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.66,0:52:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.66,0:52:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.68,0:52:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what he found was
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.68,0:52:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,when he really...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.68,0:52:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The mathematics are not on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.68,0:52:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what happened to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.68,0:52:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They fall off the bottom here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.68,0:52:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But the mathematics is quite advanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.68,0:52:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So he calibrated them,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.68,0:52:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see the levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.84,0:52:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of form a...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.35,0:53:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how they go from 100 to 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.86,0:53:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.86,0:53:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see them and suddenly at 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.86,0:53:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you see it shoot up like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.86,0:53:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and then at 600, it reaches almost infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.86,0:53:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.86,0:53:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what that means,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.86,0:53:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but I thought it looked earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.95,0:53:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's where most of mankind is in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.27,0:53:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's his consciousness level.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.27,0:53:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we at?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.27,0:53:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,207, did I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.27,0:53:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,207.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.33,0:53:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the percentage of mankind over here
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.33,0:53:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that is above 207
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.33,0:53:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually quite minimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.65,0:53:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And the great mass of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.65,0:53:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is behind us in the learning curve.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.10,0:53:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.10,0:53:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in terms of learning curve.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.15,0:53:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So 15% of mankind is above consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.15,0:53:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.31,0:54:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And Karen in our office made these graphics.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.50,0:54:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You get that the 15% is counterbalancing the 85%.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.50,0:54:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Their creativity, their power, their productivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.17,0:54:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the power that counterbalances the world
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.58,0:54:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because the power of integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.58,0:54:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is far greater than that of non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.34,0:54:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, now you understand the power of capitalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.34,0:54:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer to Karl Marx,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.38,0:54:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,this is not exploiting this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.10,0:54:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is holding it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.10,0:54:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is holding it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.29,0:54:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,One brilliant idea creates more capital
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.29,0:54:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,than all the banks in the world are holding.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.42,0:54:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Edison, one thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.67,0:55:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the giant economic productivity
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.53,0:55:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of one brilliant thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.88,0:55:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Capital exists in the mind and not in the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.88,0:55:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One brilliant thought followed up by Antigris.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.14,0:55:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest of it is just automatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.14,0:55:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the 15% that holds up the 85%.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.14,0:55:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.14,0:55:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a new thing here called PowerPoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.14,0:55:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mysterious new electronic gadget.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.23,0:55:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to flip these transparencies around.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.94,0:55:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see even the transparency flipper anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.94,0:55:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.35,0:55:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is called the PowerPoint thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.90,0:55:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to get into silent mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.08,0:55:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you have to understand how the ego works.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.08,0:56:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And one way it works is by duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.08,0:56:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And it sees everything as opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.08,0:56:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't see things as comparisons.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.08,0:56:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees them as opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.08,0:56:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.21,0:56:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So in politics, if people would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.21,0:56:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, this is the way I see it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.21,0:56:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way I would go,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.21,0:56:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and why I would go that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.21,0:56:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, politics would be Antigris.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.21,0:56:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, they think, instead of doing that,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.21,0:56:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they just hate this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.21,0:56:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Or this one hates this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.21,0:56:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say, you don't have to hate vanilla
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.40,0:56:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because you like chocolate better.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.78,0:56:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to just tell people why chocolate is better than vanilla,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.78,0:56:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don't have to hate vanilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.90,0:56:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so here we have
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.96,0:56:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,people think of heat, hot and cold
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.96,0:56:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as opposites, opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.79,0:56:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind thinks dualistically.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.79,0:56:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It sets up a positionality
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.79,0:56:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and then divides everything
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.79,0:56:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,into dualistic pairs, polarities.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.79,0:57:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This against that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.79,0:57:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This against that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.21,0:57:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this and that, but this against that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.21,0:57:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So actually we see there's only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.30,0:57:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We see with heat, where's my pointer thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.37,0:57:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to really get used to working this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.37,0:57:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see this thing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.59,0:57:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, there's only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.59,0:57:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't hot versus cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.59,0:57:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only heat, the presence of heat
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.59,0:57:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the absence of heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.01,0:57:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not two opposites of hot and absence of hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.01,0:57:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.26,0:57:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The kinesiologic response then
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.26,0:57:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is like electricity going down a wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.46,0:57:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no opposite to on.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.74,0:57:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When you turn off electricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.74,0:57:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,no offness runs down the wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.74,0:57:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either there or it ain't.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.86,0:57:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a presence or the absence of a quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.86,0:57:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have desirability.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.86,0:57:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you desire something, it's precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.86,0:58:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't desire it, you think it's awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.43,0:58:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now PowerPoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.62,0:58:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is another example.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.04,0:58:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have good versus evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.04,0:58:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got desirability.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.04,0:58:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the most obvious one to see is light.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.33,0:58:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one quality of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.58,0:58:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either present or it diminishes and it's absent.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.58,0:58:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The same with truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.58,0:58:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth either prevails
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.58,0:58:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or it becomes muddied and becomes absent.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.58,0:58:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.00,0:58:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So that takes care of duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.00,0:58:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That is to take care of it for everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.00,0:58:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We said in previous lectures
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.02,0:58:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that one can realize
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.72,0:58:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the real way to become silent
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.72,0:58:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is to become
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.72,0:58:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the potentiality of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.72,0:58:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and accept what I tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.72,0:58:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're perfectly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.72,0:58:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The past doesn't mean diddly.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.72,0:59:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The future isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.72,0:59:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the present, nothing's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.72,0:59:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's another way
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.09,0:59:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is by reflection, inner reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.60,0:59:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,By inner reflection,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.60,0:59:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,one will begin to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.60,0:59:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that the mind is silent at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.62,0:59:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If the mind were not silent,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.62,0:59:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't know that you were thinking anything
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.91,0:59:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's against the background of silence
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.91,0:59:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that you think you experience a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.55,0:59:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind itself then is the field
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.55,0:59:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in which thought occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.87,0:59:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the silence,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.87,0:59:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the backdrop of silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.29,0:59:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll explain thoughts a little bit later,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.29,0:59:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.51,0:59:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,just prior to a thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.51,0:59:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is where you'll notice the silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.51,0:59:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This silence can be noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.74,0:59:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.74,1:00:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,As I'm talking right now,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.74,1:00:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is really in a field of silence
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.34,1:00:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I'm listening to what's being said.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.63,1:00:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't the slightest idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.86,1:00:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,People say,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.86,1:00:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.86,1:00:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know what I'm going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.30,1:00:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell us what you're going to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.40,1:00:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They want three paragraphs
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.40,1:00:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,sent to their church
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.40,1:00:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to announce what you're going to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.40,1:00:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know what they're going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.78,1:00:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I can make a presumption,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.78,1:00:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so I send them some wild thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.61,1:00:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to tell them the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.50,1:00:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have the slightest idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.81,1:00:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear it at the same time you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.81,1:00:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.18,1:00:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I get a kick out of it when it's funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.18,1:00:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes it's a crack up.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.78,1:00:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the funniest thought comes out of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.78,1:01:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and it just cracks me up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.14,1:01:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,People say you laugh at your own jokes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.14,1:01:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not my jokes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.14,1:01:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where they come from.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.81,1:01:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They crack me up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.81,1:01:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If they were my joke,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.81,1:01:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they wouldn't crack me up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.00,1:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they're not my joke.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.00,1:01:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's real so funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.00,1:01:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,At all times,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.42,1:01:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,even though you're thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.42,1:01:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or think you're thinking,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.42,1:01:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is actually silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.71,1:01:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,98% of the mind is silent
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.71,1:01:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,even when you think you're thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.71,1:01:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's all your mind is thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.09,1:01:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's about 1 or 2%.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.44,1:01:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,1.85 to 3.6%.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.08,1:01:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I like how obsessive,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.08,1:01:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,make obsessive-impulsive happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.59,1:01:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you said 1.8.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.59,1:01:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, it's 1.92.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.59,1:01:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an itty-bitty part of your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.13,1:01:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is what's thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.06,1:02:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about this much of your mind here is thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.12,1:02:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest of it is entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.12,1:02:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so if only 1 or 2% of your mind is thinking,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.91,1:02:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,then how does it have so much,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.91,1:02:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,seem to have so much power over you?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.91,1:02:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have any power.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.91,1:02:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You give it the power in the secret.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.91,1:02:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you the secret of what the power is.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.91,1:02:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called hypnosis.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.91,1:02:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypnosis.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.36,1:02:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypnosis.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.36,1:02:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.90,1:02:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch my fingers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.90,1:02:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch my fingers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.90,1:02:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch my fingers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.90,1:02:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch my fingers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.90,1:02:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch my fingers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.90,1:02:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.90,1:02:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.90,1:02:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.90,1:02:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.90,1:02:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.06,1:02:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.79,1:02:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.79,1:02:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.79,1:02:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.79,1:02:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This 1% keeps you seduced.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.17,1:02:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It traps you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.52,1:02:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lure.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.52,1:02:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to be paranoid about your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.26,1:03:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to no good.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.54,1:03:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as it's got you boom-boggled,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.69,1:03:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it survives.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.69,1:03:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When it stops having you entranced
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.69,1:03:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in its hypnotic condition, lure,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.75,1:03:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it stops.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.75,1:03:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So its days are numbered.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.75,1:03:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind knows its days are numbered.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.98,1:03:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego knows its days are numbered.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.58,1:03:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, it's frantic to keep you going
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.58,1:03:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with a new worry, a new anxiety,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.58,1:03:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,a new guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.58,1:03:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does it do it?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.81,1:03:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It izes everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.81,1:03:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It izes everything, I call it,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.19,1:03:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and it seduces you through guilt,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.28,1:03:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,excitement, promise, lascivious images.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.34,1:03:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.34,1:03:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Lascivious images.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.34,1:03:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.34,1:03:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,MTV.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.49,1:03:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.49,1:03:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's got nothing else to do,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.50,1:03:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see your mind will resort
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.50,1:03:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to one of the things on the bullet board.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.66,1:04:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll politicize everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.82,1:04:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll moralize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.89,1:04:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that awful?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.89,1:04:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll idealize how things should be.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.05,1:04:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to hypothesize and rewrite history.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.40,1:04:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to romanticize things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.66,1:04:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of its favorite entertainments
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.66,1:04:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is to criticize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.66,1:04:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that awful?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.49,1:04:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's drama.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.68,1:04:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Dramatizes, emotionalizes things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.68,1:04:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalizes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.58,1:04:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,People love to get on TV and blubber.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.58,1:04:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Blubber.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.76,1:04:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.76,1:04:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They emotionalize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.76,1:04:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They dramatize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.76,1:04:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And they do that by catastrophizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.76,1:04:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Catastrophizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.69,1:04:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you theorize how it should be.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.69,1:04:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you rationalize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.88,1:04:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you fantasize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.01,1:04:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You infantilize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.01,1:04:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectualize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.01,1:04:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You mentalize everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.01,1:04:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You idealize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.01,1:05:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And you glamorize the whole process
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.01,1:05:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, I'm thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.01,1:05:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bother me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.01,1:05:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.31,1:05:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We glamorize things.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.31,1:05:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Exaggerate them because we prize them.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.31,1:05:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We like to victimize and demonize things.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.41,1:05:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So the wise give up izing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.41,1:05:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind keeps going.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.54,1:05:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got you hypnotized.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.54,1:05:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So just to know,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.60,1:05:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,98% of your mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.60,1:05:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only 1 or 2%.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.60,1:05:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no power over you
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.60,1:05:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,except the hypnotic fascination
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.14,1:05:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that you project to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.14,1:05:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So we glamorize.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.14,1:05:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Alice Bailey's book on glamor
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.14,1:05:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably the best one out of that whole series
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.14,1:05:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or one of the greatest.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.40,1:05:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was described by some spiritual teacher
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.40,1:05:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in the celestial realm.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.40,1:05:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of glamor.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.43,1:05:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist in the thing itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.43,1:05:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's something we project onto it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.43,1:06:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So we glamorize and exaggerate
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.43,1:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the importance of our mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.46,1:06:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Make it a wonderful, wonderful thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.98,1:06:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Our thoughts are really precious.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.01,1:06:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Precious.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.01,1:06:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Precious thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.49,1:06:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.48,1:06:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.67,1:06:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind has different styles
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.67,1:06:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on what level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.67,1:06:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.74,1:06:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In a group like this,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.74,1:06:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm is the big barrier.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.74,1:06:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Few people escape to level 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.90,1:06:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we say?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.90,1:06:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Point, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.90,1:06:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,4%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.90,1:06:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,4% of the population
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.90,1:06:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,ever transcend to level 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.90,1:06:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,4%, huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.96,1:06:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And to level 540, unconditional love,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.96,1:06:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,0.4%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.47,1:06:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So why is it so few people
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.47,1:06:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend the barrier of the intellect at 500?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.66,1:06:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As we've said,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.91,1:06:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein calibrated 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.91,1:07:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.91,1:07:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The great scientific geniuses of all time, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.39,1:07:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Great books of the Western world
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.39,1:07:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,run around the 460s, around there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.65,1:07:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.65,1:07:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intellect now, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.00,1:07:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,brings people up from the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.00,1:07:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So each level of consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.00,1:07:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is an improvement over the other.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.00,1:07:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, there's no point of demonizing it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.00,1:07:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you don't have enough energy to hate,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.35,1:07:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to lay down there and die.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.35,1:07:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be in apathy
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.35,1:07:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because the first rule of the ego is survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.45,1:07:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the levels of consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.58,1:07:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you transcend one.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.58,1:07:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So each one is not bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.58,1:07:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not bad in itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.18,1:07:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one is an improvement over the one below it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.25,1:07:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you can get angry,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.25,1:07:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to be in apathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.47,1:07:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Apathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.47,1:07:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why what's going on in Haiti right now
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.47,1:07:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is good.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.98,1:08:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.16,1:08:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because angriness and rebellion
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.16,1:08:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is an improvement over abject dying of poverty and AIDS
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.32,1:08:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and just laying there listlessly
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.32,1:08:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,without enough energy to even feed yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.32,1:08:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which is what happens at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.32,1:08:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So angriness is a way up over something.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.32,1:08:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, once you get beyond that,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.32,1:08:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need angriness anymore
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.32,1:08:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you give it up for courage.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.32,1:08:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you give up courage for valor.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.32,1:08:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you give up all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.32,1:08:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So each level serves its purpose biologically,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.32,1:08:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.48,1:08:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and disappears when you've transcended it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.47,1:08:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening up there?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.47,1:08:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.50,1:08:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.94,1:08:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.68,1:08:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the Newtonian mind expressing itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.68,1:08:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I hear you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.79,1:09:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The Newtonian mind, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.62,1:09:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is a tremendous advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.62,1:09:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Tremendous advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.62,1:09:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To be able to think logically,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.62,1:09:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to know the rules of logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.62,1:09:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,See,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.62,1:09:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,rationality is really a dialectic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.62,1:09:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Dialectic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.62,1:09:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In which bringing the question
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.16,1:09:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,gets you voted out
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.16,1:09:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the debating team
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.32,1:09:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's a violation
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.32,1:09:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the dialectic
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.32,1:09:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.42,1:09:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The undistributed, middle,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.42,1:09:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,all those kind of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.42,1:09:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So logic has certain rules
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.54,1:09:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which are similar to mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.54,1:09:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And people fall below
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.54,1:09:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.54,1:09:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So intellectual integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.54,1:09:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,really begins in the 400s, 410,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.54,1:09:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and then around 460,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.54,1:09:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that's really
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.86,1:09:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.86,1:09:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So I know people prefer to hate George Bush,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.44,1:09:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but I know they hate to hear it,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.44,1:09:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but he does calibrate at 460
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.50,1:09:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so he follows what
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.50,1:10:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in his world is logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.50,1:10:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.54,1:10:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It says here, by the oath of office,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.54,1:10:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I should do this, he does that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.54,1:10:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's his duty.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.59,1:10:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people see their mission differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.59,1:10:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But people in the mid-400s
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.59,1:10:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,consider their world
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.59,1:10:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to be logical, scientific,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.59,1:10:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,provable,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.59,1:10:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,based on evidence, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.88,1:10:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.88,1:10:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm of reality
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.88,1:10:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is orderly and logical
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.88,1:10:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it sees things as separate.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.88,1:10:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.04,1:10:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside it is
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.04,1:10:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of Newtonian is it divides
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.04,1:10:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the world into a dualistic
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.04,1:10:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of this causing of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.23,1:10:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you think there's a this causing of that,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.23,1:10:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be stuck in duality
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.23,1:10:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will think there's a separate
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.23,1:10:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,ego within yourself, separate from God,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.23,1:10:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of this causing of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.23,1:10:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.05,1:11:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that this morning, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.06,1:11:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics is then an advance
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.06,1:11:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.06,1:11:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,still within the linear world
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.06,1:11:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you see
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.06,1:11:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that things are not happening in an orderly fashion.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.06,1:11:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They're unpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.06,1:11:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're dealing with really is
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.16,1:11:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihoods, but not certainties.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.16,1:11:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.16,1:11:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,promises certainty.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.16,1:11:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And within certain limitations
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.16,1:11:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it does bring you to certainty.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.02,1:11:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.02,1:11:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the world we live in
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.02,1:11:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is not ruled by Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.02,1:11:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.12,1:11:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We live in a biologically real
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.12,1:11:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,earthly world
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.12,1:11:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in which subjectivity
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.12,1:11:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.12,1:11:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,most prominent factor.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.12,1:11:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It is subjectivity that gives
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.12,1:11:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.12,1:11:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.12,1:11:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,its credence.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.44,1:11:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of itself it has no credence,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.44,1:11:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but subjectively we value it
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.44,1:11:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as highly useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.60,1:12:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.30,1:12:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we go beyond that. We see that
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.30,1:12:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world of biology,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.53,1:12:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world in which we exist,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.53,1:12:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,subjectivity of our own existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.53,1:12:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, things are really quite
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.53,1:12:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,disorderly, unpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.53,1:12:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not bound.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.01,1:12:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And the most important
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.74,1:12:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,thing is the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.74,1:12:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The discovery that
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.74,1:12:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,things change just by sheer observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.74,1:12:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The effect of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.74,1:12:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.16,1:12:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein bucked.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.16,1:12:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein did not want to accept that
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.16,1:12:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,he said, I prefer to think there's
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.16,1:12:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,an independent universe out there
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.16,1:12:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists independently of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.31,1:12:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he refuted it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.31,1:12:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So he stayed at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.60,1:12:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.63,1:12:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics says that
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.79,1:12:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.79,1:12:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,predict the next thing
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.79,1:12:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that will happen with certainty.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.79,1:12:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's one digit off
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.79,1:12:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 26th decimal point
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.79,1:12:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and you run that through your computer
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.79,1:13:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,enough times, bang, you'll get a response
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.79,1:13:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that's way out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.79,1:13:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As people break their backs
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.42,1:13:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,high diving discover 13 jumps
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.42,1:13:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,killed on the 14th.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.52,1:13:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.52,1:13:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told this story before.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.62,1:13:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Two guys that used to be off
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.62,1:13:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what you would call a drive there
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.97,1:13:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,back of the Pizza Hut.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.97,1:13:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you had a rattlesnake in your yard
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.97,1:13:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd call them up.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.97,1:13:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They would come over for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.18,1:13:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They would get the rattlesnakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.18,1:13:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And they did this for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.18,1:13:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the guys
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.18,1:13:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,got bitten 19 times.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.31,1:13:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,19 times.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.60,1:13:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And the 20th time killed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.21,1:13:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,20th time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.21,1:13:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of all of them
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.21,1:13:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you presume I must now be immune.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.21,1:13:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.27,1:13:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't immune.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.50,1:13:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.78,1:13:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I tell people
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.97,1:13:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to avoid extreme sports unless you're ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.97,1:14:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.10,1:14:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough high dives
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.66,1:14:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and just as you go off
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.66,1:14:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the diving board
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.69,1:14:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you suddenly remember
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.69,1:14:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you forgot your mother's
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.69,1:14:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you forgot a Mother's Day card
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.69,1:14:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and that split 1 50th of a second
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.01,1:14:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,breaks your back.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.07,1:14:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just don't
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.07,1:14:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not too hot on extreme sports
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.07,1:14:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because I understand quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.07,1:14:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics says
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.07,1:14:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do it often enough
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.07,1:14:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,sooner or later it will get you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.33,1:14:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course we know the many sports stars
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.33,1:14:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,who push the envelope
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.33,1:14:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and they rack up.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.58,1:14:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the fact that they have driven
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.58,1:14:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,400 races
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.68,1:14:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,successfully
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.68,1:14:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that the 401th kills them.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.68,1:14:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the success
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.68,1:14:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 400
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.68,1:14:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that the 401 kills them.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.90,1:14:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's enough
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.90,1:14:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of the grim side of quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.90,1:15:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,let's go to something happier.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.41,1:15:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the enlightening
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.47,1:15:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the scale only goes up to 600
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.47,1:15:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.47,1:15:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the higher levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.89,1:15:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,See because to many people
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.89,1:15:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,God is an imagination
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.89,1:15:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that somebody thought up somewhere
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.89,1:15:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a big oppressor.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.89,1:15:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The way God is presented
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.89,1:15:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,he is an oppressor from many points
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.89,1:15:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.89,1:15:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of the liberator
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.89,1:15:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,he is the great oppressor
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.89,1:15:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the great feared God of judgment day.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.89,1:15:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So we just wanted to calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.89,1:15:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,reality
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.95,1:15:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the verifiability
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.95,1:15:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual realities
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.95,1:15:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,so with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.95,1:15:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,then we got
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.95,1:15:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the enlightenment happens at 600
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.95,1:15:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and beyond here
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.95,1:15:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the numbers of people
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.95,1:15:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,are small
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.95,1:15:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but their impact is very often large.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.95,1:15:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness in mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.95,1:15:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,goes up to a thousand
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.95,1:15:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reason it doesn't go beyond a thousand
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.95,1:15:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is because the human nervous system
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.95,1:16:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is not equipped for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.27,1:16:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to about 700 it's blissful
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.27,1:16:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,kundalini energy flows
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.27,1:16:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's exquisite
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.27,1:16:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisite
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.59,1:16:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,takes you right out of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.59,1:16:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and from there on up
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.46,1:16:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from there on up for some reason
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.46,1:16:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness may continue
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.46,1:16:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,usually it does not
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.46,1:16:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,most people over 600
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.49,1:16:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,will leave the body
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.49,1:16:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,right then
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.62,1:16:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need to stay there
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.62,1:16:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,like a near death experience
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.71,1:16:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to re-own the body
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.71,1:16:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,about 50% won't survive at all
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.71,1:16:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they just let it topple over
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.32,1:16:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but if surrounding conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.32,1:16:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure you eat and all that kind of stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.32,1:16:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the body will survive
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.32,1:16:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then it stays where it is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.32,1:16:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramana Maharishi, Nisargadatta Maharaj
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.32,1:16:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,all those are calibrated in 700
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.32,1:16:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so up to about here
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.32,1:16:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the condition is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.32,1:16:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisite
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.32,1:16:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and then sometimes it continues on up
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.32,1:17:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it is not exquisite
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.32,1:17:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it is extraordinarily painful at times
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.32,1:17:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,excruciatingly painful
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.32,1:17:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Buddha said that
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.32,1:17:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ striped blood
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.32,1:17:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and from there on up
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.32,1:17:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the human nervous system is just not equipped
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.32,1:17:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle energies
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.32,1:17:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,over 700
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.32,1:17:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and to go over that level
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.32,1:17:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,causes a great deal of
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.58,1:17:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering, inner suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.58,1:17:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, gradually the nerves do begin
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.58,1:17:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.58,1:17:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,greater capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.58,1:17:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they pull in more protein molecules
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.58,1:17:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and they actually do modify
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.58,1:17:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but it takes some years
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.58,1:17:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes some years
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.58,1:17:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and the techniques advance
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.58,1:17:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so it is better to not worry about that
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.58,1:17:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,here in this realm
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.58,1:17:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it is better to go to some heavenly realm
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.58,1:17:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and do that
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.28,1:17:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so then just for fun
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.28,1:17:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we asked what is an archangel
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.28,1:17:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we got 50,000 and up
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.28,1:17:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,50,000 and up, yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.34,1:17:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was in the pits of hell
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.34,1:17:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and I asked
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.44,1:18:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.82,1:18:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed to him for help
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.85,1:18:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the pits of hell
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.91,1:18:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,eternal hell
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.91,1:18:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the pits of hell are eternal
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.91,1:18:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially eternal
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.91,1:18:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,eternal with no hope
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.91,1:18:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the certainty of no hope
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.64,1:18:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is so profound
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.64,1:18:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you will never
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.12,1:18:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,leave this state ever
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.12,1:18:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get what ever means
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.12,1:18:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then dread
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.60,1:18:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,takes on a dimension
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.60,1:18:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't know it could take
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.08,1:18:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of that
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.08,1:18:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the voice within said
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.08,1:18:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God I ask him for help
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.07,1:18:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and then out of that
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.07,1:18:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,oblivion
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.23,1:18:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then out of oblivion and nothingness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.23,1:18:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly the infinite presence
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.23,1:18:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.83,1:18:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,why I got into that anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.24,1:18:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that heaven and hell
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.26,1:19:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,are then experiential
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.26,1:19:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,while still in a physical body
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.26,1:19:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,people worry about it later
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.26,1:19:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it's experiential right here right now
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.26,1:19:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of one's own decisions
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.26,1:19:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,let's move on to the next one
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.26,1:19:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yes
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.26,1:19:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangel
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.26,1:19:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what started that
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.26,1:19:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I always think some cruising Archangel
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.26,1:19:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,some Archangel cruising by
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.26,1:19:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,heard this little
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.26,1:19:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,flippy thought
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.26,1:19:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God I ask him for help
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.26,1:19:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and he went hmm
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.26,1:19:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and went on
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.96,1:19:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,knocked me out of the world for 30 years
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.12,1:19:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,30 years I never said anything
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.18,1:19:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I was silent within
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.18,1:19:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I left the world and came out here
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.50,1:19:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,hmm
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.73,1:19:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,never mentioned anything until 1995
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.18,1:19:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it just is such a shock
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.18,1:19:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just like pow
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.24,1:19:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of it hits you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.27,1:19:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mind is knocked silent
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.27,1:19:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so the silence of the mind is the automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.27,1:19:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of a automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.27,1:20:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of a level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.27,1:20:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which transcends thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.27,1:20:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in that state
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.27,1:20:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,there is nothing to think
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.27,1:20:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no person to think
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.66,1:20:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no somebody to think
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.75,1:20:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because somebody-ness is left
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.75,1:20:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no person to think
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.90,1:20:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no this to think about
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.90,1:20:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or that
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.90,1:20:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so thinkingness is not
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.90,1:20:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,part of that state
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.51,1:20:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,through witnessing then
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.51,1:20:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we begin to see
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.51,1:20:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind looks at form
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.51,1:20:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it registers form
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.51,1:20:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it recognizes it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.51,1:20:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and some spiritual teachers say
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.51,1:20:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,identify with this here the watcher
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.51,1:20:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer and the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.51,1:20:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of being part of the content of the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.51,1:20:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,merely witness it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.51,1:20:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll move to the next exciting slide
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.15,1:20:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll move to the next
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.15,1:20:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting slide
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.15,1:21:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,what
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.54,1:21:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the maps
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.99,1:21:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yeah we'll do everything
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.41,1:21:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,this is our home team here
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.14,1:21:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,did the maps come up next
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.14,1:21:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yes well this is quite
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.21,1:21:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you know we predicted Haiti
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.21,1:21:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple of years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.21,1:21:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we said here's North America
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.21,1:21:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated levels
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.43,1:21:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.43,1:21:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there's group karma
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.69,1:21:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,there's group karma
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.01,1:21:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you belong to a group
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.01,1:21:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of your level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.01,1:21:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're ascribed to that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.58,1:21:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,then that group comes on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.58,1:21:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to be in certain areas on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.26,1:21:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,does what it does
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.26,1:21:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,either improves its karmic potential
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.26,1:21:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or makes it worse
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.26,1:21:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,then we tend to come back again
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.26,1:21:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in karmic groups
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.26,1:21:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see if that's so
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.58,1:21:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest good
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.58,1:22:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to be a person
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.58,1:22:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,there is like group karma
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.58,1:22:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're seeing
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.58,1:22:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,right in Haiti now
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.58,1:22:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is like group karma
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.58,1:22:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,all the great tragedies on mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.58,1:22:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,here you've got the western hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.58,1:22:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Greenland
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.58,1:22:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,345, America
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.58,1:22:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Canada 410, 420
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.58,1:22:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Central America in the 300s
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.58,1:22:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not going to get any trouble
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.61,1:22:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,from the whole western hemisphere here
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.61,1:22:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they're in the high 200s, they're all over 200
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.61,1:22:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,right in the middle of it
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.61,1:22:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to turn this thing on here
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.61,1:22:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,there
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.61,1:22:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we said wow like a big boil
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.61,1:22:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,on your leg
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.95,1:22:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,here's trouble
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.95,1:22:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got a 55 in the middle of the 300s
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.95,1:22:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the 400s
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.40,1:22:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we said that a year or two ago
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.49,1:22:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,55 then
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.49,1:22:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,so this is some karmic group
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.49,1:22:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes on this way
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.94,1:22:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and they've got to evolve beyond it
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.94,1:22:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what can we do to help Haiti
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.35,1:23:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,well I think
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.35,1:23:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.35,1:23:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and inspire
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.35,1:23:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,through beauty, through excellence
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.42,1:23:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,through demonstrating compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.42,1:23:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.42,1:23:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to send troops there
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.42,1:23:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what our troops are going to do in Haiti
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.42,1:23:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but they're going to go there I guess
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.15,1:23:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really strange
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.15,1:23:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we let Mexicans cross the border
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.15,1:23:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don't let Haitians cross the border
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.15,1:23:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if they're trying to swim to safety
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.15,1:23:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,why do we put them back
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.15,1:23:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, we do that with Cuba
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.60,1:23:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the peculiarities of politics
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.60,1:23:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which I understand
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.60,1:23:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't really want to understand them
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.82,1:23:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,not bad enough as it is
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.82,1:23:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway so we have our preferences
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.82,1:23:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and our favorites
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.82,1:23:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's human nature
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.82,1:23:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so right in the middle of all these numbers
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.82,1:23:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got a 55
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.05,1:23:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and they stand out so strongly
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.05,1:23:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that's got to be some kind of a karmic group
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.05,1:23:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's certain things about their culture
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.21,1:24:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that would make 55
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.21,1:24:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you would understand why it's 55
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.21,1:24:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been there
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.21,1:24:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's certain things about their culture
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.21,1:24:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that would pretty much guarantee that
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.21,1:24:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,ok let's go to the next one
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.21,1:24:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting trip around the world
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.03,1:24:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we calibrate all the
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.03,1:24:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,countries in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.03,1:24:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,all the continents
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.48,1:24:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and we learn a great deal
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.48,1:24:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,here's Australia at 410
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.61,1:24:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,here you've got 405
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.61,1:24:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,here you've got India at 355
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.61,1:24:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got China at 305
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.61,1:24:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you know China is evolving
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.61,1:24:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,China is really coming out of the
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.61,1:24:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Marxian collapse
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.61,1:24:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mayoism
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.61,1:24:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective farms
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.77,1:24:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.77,1:24:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl Marx calibrated at 130
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.77,1:24:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so the downside of Marxism is
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.77,1:24:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is starvation
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.77,1:24:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and revolution and disaster
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.77,1:24:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the great books of the rest of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.90,1:24:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx stands out
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.90,1:24:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they're all in the 400s
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.90,1:25:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and Marx is at 130
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.90,1:25:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so if by their fruits you shall know them
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.90,1:25:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say too much for
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.90,1:25:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Marxism as a lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.09,1:25:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway we see that China is evolving
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.09,1:25:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,they have increasing property rights
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.09,1:25:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,civil rights
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.09,1:25:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,etc
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.09,1:25:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,religion and spirituality is still not
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.09,1:25:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,welcomed there
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.09,1:25:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's sort of a threat to the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.09,1:25:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,strict secularism
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.37,1:25:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the book Power Versus Force
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.37,1:25:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,published in China
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.37,1:25:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I was told you've got to clean God out of the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.37,1:25:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.40,1:25:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and just express it as energy consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.40,1:25:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,energy
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.40,1:25:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,replace God with higher energy
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.40,1:25:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can get posed in China
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.40,1:25:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as you've got God in there
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.40,1:25:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so they've got a way of
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.69,1:25:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,censoring things
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.94,1:25:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah but still
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.94,1:25:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,China has come up a long way
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.94,1:25:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,now it has a new
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.94,1:25:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,premiere
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.94,1:25:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a group we were at in California
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.94,1:25:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,some years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.98,1:26:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of course the miracles group
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.98,1:26:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and we decided the group would take on China
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.98,1:26:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,take on China as a
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.14,1:26:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,group project
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.33,1:26:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,since then China has come up
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.36,1:26:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so I don't want to thank anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.36,1:26:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,who's here from California for that miracles group
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.36,1:26:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wasn't for you folks
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.36,1:26:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,China would still be down
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.36,1:26:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.06,1:26:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so the new premiere of China
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.06,1:26:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is moving ahead
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.06,1:26:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so you get very interesting theory
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.06,1:26:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,here you have Mongolia up here
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.06,1:26:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,great expanses
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.06,1:26:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,here's where the trouble is
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.06,1:26:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we said North Africa
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.06,1:26:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,North Africa is where the trouble is
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.06,1:26:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's basically a large karmic group
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.06,1:26:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got two countries
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.06,1:26:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,one at 190 and one at 192
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.06,1:26:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly warring at each other
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.06,1:26:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but they've been doing that for
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.06,1:26:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple thousand years
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.06,1:26:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so I don't know if they're going to
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.06,1:26:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,decide to stop or not
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.06,1:26:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but anyway they get too much out of it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.06,1:26:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole country is built on
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.06,1:26:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,built on the structure
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.06,1:27:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of strife and conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.06,1:27:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.22,1:27:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we blow up a busload of children
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.22,1:27:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and they bomb our school
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.22,1:27:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and the police
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.73,1:27:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and they send a rocket
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.73,1:27:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's a whole lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.82,1:27:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if they wanted to stop it
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.82,1:27:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,they would
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.12,1:27:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,people tell you one thing
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.11,1:27:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but if that was so
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.11,1:27:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be so
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.11,1:27:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's not so
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.37,1:27:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and we get to this
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.37,1:27:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they calibrate it 190 and 185
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.40,1:27:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which is below the level of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.40,1:27:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,so whatever they say is not so
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.01,1:27:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it serves that positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.04,1:27:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's very interesting to them
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.04,1:27:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,see here's Uganda
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.04,1:27:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where the UN is
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.04,1:27:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,where all these things are happening
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.04,1:27:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and people want to turn our country over at 421
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.04,1:27:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to the UN which calibrates about 195
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.04,1:27:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't make any sense to me at all
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.04,1:27:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean where are they with Haiti
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.04,1:27:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,where are they with Uganda
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.04,1:28:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what they do
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.04,1:28:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they pass out parcels of food
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.04,1:28:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so they're like an extension to me of the Red Cross
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.04,1:28:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and they do a lot of good
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.04,1:28:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but I wouldn't turn the rule of our country over to them
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.04,1:28:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so here you've got Africa
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.17,1:28:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and here you've got Europe
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.17,1:28:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and here you've got Uganda
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.17,1:28:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you see you're around 50 or so
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.17,1:28:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the slaughtering of people there
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.17,1:28:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.65,1:28:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the calibrated levels then
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.65,1:28:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,show a distribution somehow
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.65,1:28:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,now Europe has become secularized
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.65,1:28:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,where is Europe here
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.65,1:28:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened to Europe
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.65,1:28:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,300 is up in here
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.03,1:28:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,see America
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.03,1:28:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the constitution of the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.03,1:28:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates around 700
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.60,1:28:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest of any country in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.60,1:28:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the government itself calibrates extremely high
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.60,1:28:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you can criticize it
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.50,1:28:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's a matter of fact
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.50,1:28:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,if you calibrate it's the highest in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.50,1:28:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it is integrity by intent
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.50,1:28:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that it's perfect
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.50,1:28:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that it's saintly
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.50,1:29:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not saintly
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.50,1:29:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a government is not supposed to be saintly
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.50,1:29:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's supposed to protect its people
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.50,1:29:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so here we have
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.17,1:29:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens with non-integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.17,1:29:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,then is
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.17,1:29:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,things go downhill
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.65,1:29:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but they only go downhill a little bit
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.65,1:29:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if you stop at saintly
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.65,1:29:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,secularism then you're in
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.65,1:29:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,usually the high 200s or 300s
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.65,1:29:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that means
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.65,1:29:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't mean you're not responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.65,1:29:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just that you eliminate God
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.65,1:29:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,from the equation
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.65,1:29:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you eliminate God from the equation
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.65,1:29:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,which is from a certain viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.65,1:29:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's fine with me
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.65,1:29:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care if they do it
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.65,1:29:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't care about it
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.84,1:29:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so whatever they want to do
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.84,1:29:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,alright let's move on to the next country
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.87,1:29:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so here's the western hemisphere again
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.87,1:29:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why it recurred
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.33,1:29:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,well let's go on
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.33,1:29:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we already saw the western hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.81,1:29:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,here's the other hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.81,1:29:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,well because I thought these are easier to read
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.81,1:30:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the other was too full of data
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.81,1:30:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you see New Zealand and Australia
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.97,1:30:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,would be good places to live
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.97,1:30:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't they
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.97,1:30:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that's 400
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.97,1:30:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,355
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.97,1:30:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,all these higher calibrations
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.97,1:30:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if you want to retire
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.97,1:30:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I would retire to a higher calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.00,1:30:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,here's where it's 40
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.00,1:30:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not a good place to retire
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.22,1:30:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there are the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.28,1:30:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you call those things
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.78,1:30:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,gorillas
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.51,1:30:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and the gorillas calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.58,1:30:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than the people there
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.43,1:30:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I would rather sit for breakfast
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.43,1:30:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with a mountain gorilla
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.46,1:30:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,than the people who work there
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.13,1:30:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,alright we'll move on to the next
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.83,1:30:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can't say
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.21,1:30:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,anything about it
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.21,1:31:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,except that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.30,1:31:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if we study the world
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.30,1:31:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,this is what we find
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.34,1:31:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and North Africa we spend a little extra time on
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.34,1:31:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know it's so much in the news
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.34,1:31:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Iraq and all such like
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.34,1:31:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.34,1:31:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple of the countries I was talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.34,1:31:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you see are at the top
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.34,1:31:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can see they are not devoted to peace
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.34,1:31:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore all this
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.34,1:31:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation about it is conversation
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.34,1:31:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and Iraq as a country
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.34,1:31:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was also far
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.34,1:31:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,away from peace
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.34,1:31:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Syria has come up since we did this map
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.34,1:31:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,if you recalibrate Syria
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.34,1:31:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see it came up
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.34,1:31:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and Gaddafi has somehow gotten religion all of a sudden
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.34,1:31:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for which we're all quite happy
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.55,1:31:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell you the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.55,1:31:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Time magazine came out
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.71,1:31:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so let's go to the next one
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.81,1:31:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the trouble zones
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.81,1:31:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we're in North Africa
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.81,1:31:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,where we've experienced them
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.81,1:31:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so we ask now what is the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.81,1:31:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you see because the human mind
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.81,1:31:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,can't tell truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.90,1:32:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the human mind is impressionable
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.74,1:32:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the masters of rhetoric
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.74,1:32:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you know rhetoric political persuasiveness
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.74,1:32:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,has been
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.77,1:32:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a formal study
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.77,1:32:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,well in the year 350 BC
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.77,1:32:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so for the book I'm doing now
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.06,1:32:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very sharp on it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.06,1:32:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to reread Plato, Aristotle and Socrates
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.06,1:32:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and the refutation
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.06,1:32:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of the argument
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.06,1:32:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the philosophic position of the sophist
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.06,1:32:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.15,1:32:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,what could be
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.66,1:32:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,saved from all of that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.66,1:32:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,would be some
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.66,1:32:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,rhetoric
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.66,1:32:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the good side of rhetoric
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.66,1:32:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you present truth in a way
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.66,1:32:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that is palatable to the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.02,1:32:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,now
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.08,1:32:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,truth is not always palatable
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.08,1:32:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.08,1:32:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact truth is often
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.08,1:32:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the last thing people want to hear
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.14,1:32:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so I warn people
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.14,1:32:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I warn people
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.14,1:32:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're interested in truth
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.50,1:32:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have to pull in
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.50,1:33:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,positionalities
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.06,1:33:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of the new book
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.06,1:33:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm forgetting what it is already
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.06,1:33:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's going to be truth versus fallacy
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.06,1:33:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,truth versus fallacy
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.06,1:33:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you decide something like that
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.06,1:33:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's always
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.06,1:33:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,truth versus fallacy
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.19,1:33:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened to the war
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.86,1:33:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,oh okay
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.86,1:33:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we were doing World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.86,1:33:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can take all the events
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.86,1:33:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of any major thing in history
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.86,1:33:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they say if you haven't learned from history
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.86,1:33:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to repeat it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.86,1:33:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see mankind has repeated it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.86,1:33:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,over and over again
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.86,1:33:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so what is the lesson that we should have learned
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.86,1:33:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so that this doesn't keep repeating itself
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.66,1:33:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we learned that
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.66,1:33:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,peace is the automatic consequence of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.66,1:33:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the automatic consequence of falsity
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.66,1:33:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it's as simple as that
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.66,1:33:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,where truth prevails
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.21,1:33:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,peace prevails
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.21,1:33:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's an automatic consequence of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.37,1:33:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so peace is not something
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.37,1:33:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you can force on people
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.53,1:34:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or we'll kill you
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.49,1:34:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.49,1:34:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because the Iraqi war is still somewhat
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.49,1:34:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalized in people's minds
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.49,1:34:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we should probably stay away from it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.62,1:34:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and what we do
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.62,1:34:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll go back to my earlier life
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.62,1:34:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and see how did people calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.62,1:34:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and how did a war
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.62,1:34:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest war in history
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.62,1:34:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,kill more people than any other war
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.62,1:34:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,how could such a thing happen
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.62,1:34:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so we put the calibrations
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.10,1:34:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we just calibrated people
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.10,1:34:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see very interesting things
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.10,1:34:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Winston Churchill at 510
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.10,1:34:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,now Winston Churchill
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.51,1:34:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,when he said
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.61,1:34:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in England before World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.61,1:34:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that war is coming and you'd better get yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.61,1:34:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,ready for it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.61,1:34:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they thought
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.15,1:34:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler was a war monger
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.15,1:34:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so they threw him out
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.15,1:34:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and they brought in a gentleman
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.15,1:34:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who said he was going to bring peace in our times
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.15,1:34:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,peace in our times
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.18,1:34:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.47,1:35:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.76,1:35:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Churchill was a realist
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.76,1:35:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,he says I don't like the idea of it
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.76,1:35:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but you know frankly folks
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.76,1:35:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler's going to take over
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.89,1:35:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'd better be prepared
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.89,1:35:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,he was thrown out as a war monger
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.89,1:35:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pacifists who calibrated 145
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.89,1:35:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as exempted by Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.89,1:35:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at 185
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.89,1:35:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,became friendly with Hitler
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.89,1:35:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when Erwin Churchill's hand
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.89,1:35:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they signed a peace treaty
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.40,1:35:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they signed a peace treaty
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.40,1:35:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody who signs a peace treaty
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.46,1:35:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with somebody who calibrates
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.46,1:35:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.46,1:35:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,by the end of the war
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.46,1:35:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Adolf Hitler calibrated about 145
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.46,1:35:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so here you got somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.46,1:35:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,who's in denial
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.46,1:35:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,at 185 full of sophistry
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.46,1:35:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,all about peace and all that stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.87,1:35:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're signing a contract
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.87,1:35:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,with this guy here
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.61,1:35:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you've got
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.61,1:35:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what you've got is
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.61,1:35:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,wishful thinking naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.79,1:36:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,oh if we're just nice to them
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.79,1:36:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll be nice to us
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.79,1:36:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so damn
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.34,1:36:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,he'll be nice to us
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.34,1:36:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,he won't torture people
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.34,1:36:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to death so slowly
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.34,1:36:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,right
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.75,1:36:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,oh so delusion
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.18,1:36:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so that when the chips fell
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.18,1:36:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,then
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.89,1:36:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the war started
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.89,1:36:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and they had to pull Winston out
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.89,1:36:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Winston was at 510
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.88,1:36:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,wow
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.88,1:36:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,well we did
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.88,1:36:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the energy of
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.88,1:36:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,when we spoke at Oxford
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.88,1:36:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we stopped off in Scotland
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.88,1:36:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and did
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.88,1:36:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the Scottish Tattoo
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.07,1:36:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a military musical
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.07,1:36:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,extravaganza
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.07,1:36:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,put on in front of the palace
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.42,1:36:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,once a year
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.42,1:36:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and we heard 100 bagpipes
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.42,1:36:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,imagine 100 pipers
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.42,1:36:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,walking across
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.42,1:37:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the sound of it just made the hair on the back of your head stand right up
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.90,1:37:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we said
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.90,1:37:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,what is magical
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.90,1:37:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,there's something different about the sound of bagpipes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.44,1:37:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that has nothing to do with music
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.44,1:37:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,no
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.63,1:37:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the most dreaded sound
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.63,1:37:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in the history of warfare
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.63,1:37:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is the sound of another army coming towards you
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.63,1:37:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with the background of the sound of bagpipes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.63,1:37:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,more scary
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.73,1:37:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,than the screams of the
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.73,1:37:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Viking warriors
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.73,1:37:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,more terrifying than any
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.14,1:37:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when you because there's an energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.14,1:37:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at 505
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.56,1:37:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,505
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.56,1:37:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.02,1:37:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,505
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.02,1:37:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you better make sure you've
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.28,1:37:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,signed your will
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.28,1:37:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,505
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.82,1:37:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is death
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.82,1:37:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,505
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.95,1:37:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you see is not just courage
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.95,1:37:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,so the average warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.95,1:38:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,transcends fear
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.95,1:38:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,505
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.02,1:38:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we've all walked into a hail of bullets
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.02,1:38:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.02,1:38:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's how you get over 200
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.02,1:38:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the one in childbirth does the same thing
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.02,1:38:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,she knows she's risking her life
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.02,1:38:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,most women in history
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.43,1:38:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,died in childbirth
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.43,1:38:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so by the act of heroism
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.14,1:38:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for others
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.20,1:38:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sacredness of life
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.20,1:38:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,she puts her life
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.26,1:38:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,on the line
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.26,1:38:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and frankly she used to lose it often
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.26,1:38:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,she lost it often
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.19,1:38:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In the family Bible I have at home, the man was often married three or four times,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.14,1:38:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and many of the children died.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.38,1:38:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So the man goes over 200 when he's willing to face death for some higher principle,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.80,1:38:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,honor, love of country, to defend the homeland.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.39,1:38:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,505 is something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.27,1:39:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,505 is valor.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.19,1:39:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Valor calibrates 505.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.61,1:39:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In valor, you're not trying to prove anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.09,1:39:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to prove that you're not subject to fear anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.47,1:39:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You proved that long ago at Calibration 11-200.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.69,1:39:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, 505 is being what you are in the face of all that is,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.87,1:39:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to be exactly who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.43,1:39:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's extremely powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.21,1:39:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see Winston at 510 was the,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.01,1:39:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,hmm,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.61,1:39:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,was the spiritual strength of the bulldog.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.40,1:39:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The bulldog.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.40,1:39:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Roosevelt very close to him at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.06,1:39:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,President Truman, God bless him, he inherited a terrible problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.36,1:39:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He had to decide about the nuclear bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.80,1:39:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody envied him.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.78,1:39:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And that involves triage.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.08,1:40:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to kill 200,000 to save the life of 6 or 7 million or not?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.58,1:40:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody likes to be faced.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.28,1:40:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Every triage, every physician faces it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.29,1:40:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I faced it many a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.89,1:40:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The life of the mother, the life of the child.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.05,1:40:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So triage then is, was the problem that Truman faced.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.93,1:40:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And happily, he was at 495, which nobody would have predicted.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.34,1:40:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember my father's description of Truman as being a haberdasher from someplace.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.28,1:40:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God help us, he says.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.94,1:40:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A haberdasher from Missouri or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.10,1:40:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,God help us.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.98,1:40:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when called upon,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.66,1:40:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy came up in Truman.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.08,1:40:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And he did the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.88,1:40:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,None of us would want his decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.16,1:40:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If he said no, 7 million people would have died.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.12,1:40:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,7 million because you had the moral cowardice not to say yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.84,1:40:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say yes, you're going to be vilified in history as having killed 200,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.10,1:40:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're either going to be attacked one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.54,1:41:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So should it be for the death of 200,000 or the death of 7 million?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.60,1:41:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the estimated death...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.76,1:41:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The death rate if we invaded Japan was at least 7 million, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.63,1:41:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we have MacArthur and all these people.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.41,1:41:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see Wernher von Braun, Heisenberg, the U.S. military.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.87,1:41:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The concept of triage itself is not well understood in America.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.69,1:41:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's understood very well in medicine.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.51,1:41:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Los Alamos, you can see what the intention of all these people were.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.61,1:41:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting, you see the kamikaze pilot.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.97,1:41:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the kamikaze pilot.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.03,1:41:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the kamikaze pilot.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.05,1:41:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The pilot was already an integrous warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.83,1:41:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So was the Luftwaffe, integrous warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.91,1:41:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't do it to prove anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.91,1:41:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They did it out of duty.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.81,1:41:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hirohito's right on the edge at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.83,1:41:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Tojo's at 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.89,1:41:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And Yamamoto had a certain amount of wisdom
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.15,1:41:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because right from the beginning he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.85,1:41:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,well, we're going to lose this war.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.73,1:42:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto was not popular because he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.19,1:42:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.91,1:42:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw that right from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.89,1:42:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We've awakened the sleeping giant.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.48,1:42:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's see what else is going on here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.62,1:42:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Oppenheimer, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.78,1:42:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,then there were double agents in Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.72,1:42:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look at pictures of people and calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.98,1:42:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell who's going to be the double agent
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.16,1:42:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because their consciousness is out.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.20,1:42:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So they can disguise their appearance
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.80,1:42:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they do and what they say,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.04,1:42:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but they cannot disguise their level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.10,1:42:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want people to work on a secret project
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.08,1:42:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that puts all of mankind at risk,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.16,1:42:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you better calibrate their level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.44,1:42:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of them are going to sell out,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.08,1:42:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and a certain number of them do.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.55,1:42:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The Cambridge Five sold out.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.53,1:42:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were the intellectuals coming out of England.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.26,1:42:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The traders all calibrated 40 or 50.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.00,1:42:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the League of Nations wasn't doing much better
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.26,1:42:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,than the current, what do they call it, UN thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.49,1:43:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The League of Nations didn't do anything to stop World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.91,1:43:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,any more than...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.16,1:43:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the UN's doing much of anything now.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.30,1:43:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Pacifism, the attack on Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.60,1:43:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph Goebbels is very interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.24,1:43:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because we learn from history.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.08,1:43:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What Goebbels exploited was the naivete of the human mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.34,1:43:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew people can't tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.88,1:43:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you repeat falsehood often enough,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.02,1:43:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,people will believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.68,1:43:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the position, then, that the human ego gets into.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.66,1:43:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it has a warped view, it repeats it many times
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.08,1:43:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and then becomes conditioned.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.44,1:43:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the London Blitz, Dr. Mengele, the Rosenbergs.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.69,1:43:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,People still worry about the Rosenbergs.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.41,1:43:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And Lord Ha-Ha, I always got a kick out of calibrating him,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.85,1:43:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was 50.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.05,1:43:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Ha-Ha, I forget his real name,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.19,1:43:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but he was a defector that used to be on radio
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.61,1:43:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with pro-Nazi propaganda.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.27,1:44:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.50,1:44:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if you do all the famous wars in history,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.24,1:44:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you learn incredibly important things.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.98,1:44:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.01,1:44:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Break what?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.58,1:44:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take a break.
